Center: Centre for Photonuclear Experiments Data, Moscow State University, Russia
title: Cross sections for photoneutron emission induced by lithium gamma rays.

x4freetext: Cross sections for photoneutron emission induced
by lithium gamma rays.

x4codes.hlp: University of Pennsylvania, Philadelphia, PA, United States of America

x4freetext: Lithium proton-capture gamma rays were obtained  from
of  narrow line at 17.6 MeV and a broad line at 14.8
MeV.  All gamma rays were associated  with  441  keV
resonance.  The  relative intensity of 17.6 and 14.8
MeV components was about 1.7 : 1.

x4codes.hlp: University of Pennsylvania, Philadelphia, PA, United States of America

x4freetext: With energy of protons 0.48 MeV.
High-purity powder  samples  of thirteen elements (of
atomic  numbers  ranging  from  26   to   83)   were
irradiated  in  thin aluminum cylindrical containers
which fit over the proton beam tube and thus subtend
almost the total solid angle at the lithium target.
A cylindrical crystal 1.5 inch  by  1.5  inch
was used to monitor the gamma rays intensity. (BF3).
Two groups of four counters (1 inch diameter by  4.5
inch  active length) were used.  One group (Group A)
of 4 counters consisted of two  counters  above  and
two  counters  below  the  sample.  The second group
(Group B) of 4 counters formed a square array  above
the  sample  at  90 degr.  to the protons beam.  The
counters of this group were  placed  closer  to  the
target.
To determine  the  absolute  energy  of  the  neutron
counters Ra-Be neutrons source were used, calibrated
by the National Bureau of  Standards.  Its  absolute
strength was estimated to be 5%.
With  data of early experimental measurements.
The efficiency of detection systems was measured for
different energy of neutrons.
The cross sections for photoneutron  production  were
calculated from neutron yields,  which were measured
at all energies of gamma rays.  The  efficiency  for
the  Group A of counters does not depend on neutrons
energy.  The efficiency for the Group B of  counters
depends  strongly  on  the  neutrons energy (near to
The energies of lithium gamma line are  presented  as
high  and low values of limit of gamma quanta energy
Eg-min and Eg-max, respectively.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The relative cross-section values for
the different elements are known to better than 10%.
The  uncertainty  in  absolute  value of each
cross section  obtained  with  the  Group  A  neutron
counters   to  be  15%,  determined  chiefly  by  the
uncertainties in  the  neutron  and  photon  detector
efficiencies.
Since the  results  for  Group  B   depend   on   the
assumptions   made   about  the  photoneutron  energy
spectra,  authors believe the Group A  values  to  be
more accurate than those obtained with Group B.
